{"TopicId":167161,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Helicopter not working (firespitter mod)","CreatedByName":"Dragonwarp","CreatedById":181590,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-03T21:11:58Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Dragonwarp","CreatedById":181590,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-03T21:11:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have this helicopter that I\u0027m making with firespitter, and it keeps on flipping out whenever I launch. Any tips? FYI: My center on lift is on top of my center of mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-03T21:40:48Z\u0022 title=\u002211/03/2017 09:40  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Dragonwarp\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman1791","CreatedById":103062,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T01:26:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs your center of thrust in line with your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E? If not that\u0027ll be creating a\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Elot\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0of torque. Unless you have more than a couple stubby wings, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E shouldn\u0027t matter much. If you do have wings, for a heli it should be above and maybe a bit behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-04T01:27:46Z\u0022 title=\u002211/04/2017 01:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 4, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Dman1791\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dragonwarp","CreatedById":181590,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T19:49:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223210526\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167161\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509758786\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103062\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dman1791\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, Dman1791 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs your center of thrust in line with your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E? If not that\u0027ll be creating a\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Elot\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0of torque. Unless you have more than a couple stubby wings, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E shouldn\u0027t matter much. If you do have wings, for a heli it should be above and maybe a bit behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat definitely helped, but it still flips out, just slower, and I can\u0027t really control it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman1791","CreatedById":103062,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T20:01:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHm. How is it flipping? Forward, backward, sideways? If it\u0027s sideways, you might have a symmetry problem. Forwards or backwards, center of thrust is still off most likely. Also, do you have a tail rotor?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dragonwarp","CreatedById":181590,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T20:44:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223211027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167161\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509825689\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103062\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dman1791\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, Dman1791 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHm. How is it flipping? Forward, backward, sideways? If it\u0027s sideways, you might have a symmetry problem. Forwards or backwards, center of thrust is still off most likely. Also, do you have a tail rotor?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Yes, I have a tail rotor,and it starts flipping sideways, then backwards AND sideways at the same time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-04T20:45:45Z\u0022 title=\u002211/04/2017 08:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 4, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Dragonwarp\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman1791","CreatedById":103062,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T20:46:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs everything perfectly symmetrical? Also, it\u0027s flipping, not just spinning, right? If everything is symmetrical I\u0027m not sure I can help any further. Maybe a screen of the craft with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E markers on\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dragonwarp","CreatedById":181590,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T20:58:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223211076\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167161\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509828394\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103062\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dman1791\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Dman1791 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs everything perfectly symmetrical? Also, it\u0027s flipping, not just spinning, right? If everything is symmetrical I\u0027m not sure I can help any further. Maybe a screen of the craft with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E markers on\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep. It\u0027s flipping, not just spinning.and I\u0027m 90% sure that everything is where it should be (I think. . .).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}